## Key Findings
- Default configurations expose critical vulnerabilities
- Lack of authentication enables enumeration attacks
- SMTP misconfiguration allows spoofing and phishing

## Mitigations
- Use SNMPv3 (authentication + encryption)
- Disable unused services
- Implement SPF, DKIM, DMARC
- Restrict access via firewall rules

